      {
        "id": 2386058,
        "name": "Barry Rothof",
        "username": "Barry_Rothof",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/barry_rothof/{size}/1215_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-03-27T22:18:32.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>5 of us gathered @ The Chefs Table of Restaurant Callas</p>\n<p><strong>Oyster with beef tenderloin and horseradish</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Jacques Selosse Champagne Grand Cru Blanc de Noirs Extra Brut La C\u00f4te Faron</strong><br>\nLovely bouquet of bruised apple and pastry cream. Glossy ample with lovely energy and considerable depth and dimension. A lot of pleasure ! <strong>(93 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>J\u00e9r\u00f4me Pr\u00e9vost La Closerie Fac-Simile</strong><br>\nTense core of fruit, searing intense, bright and very compelling with good intensity and energy. Stunning ! <strong>(94 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Tartelette with scallops, parmesan and winter truffle</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2007 Fran\u00e7ois Raveneau Chablis 1er Cru Mont\u00e9e de Tonnerre</strong><br>\nNotes of citrus, lime on an elegant palate with succulent acidity and a taut finish. <strong>(92 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>2014 Jean-Claude Ramonet Chassagne-Montrachet 1er Cru Les Ruchottes</strong><br>\nSuperb! White stone fruit, cream and chalky soil. cool, glossy and refined with perfect balance. Accessible and totally delicious! <strong>(94 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Baked cod with brandade of crustaceans, duckliver, eel and winter truffle</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2009 Cecile Tremblay Nuits St. Georges 1er Cru Aux Murgers</strong><br>\nClassic, spice nose of black fruit. Very concentrated on the palate with a deep core of fruit concealing rich tannins and leading to a precise long finish. <strong>(93 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>2009 Domaine Rossignol Trapet Chambertin</strong><br>\nElegant cherry-berry and fine, supple tannins underpinned by bright acidity. Pretty! <strong>(92 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Roasted veal tenderloin with beef marrow, parsly and saus \u2018Marchand de Vin\u2019</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2007 Domaine Fourrier Griotte-Chambertin Vieille Vigne</strong><br>\nExquisite elegance. Delicate sweet red cherry and sapid earth, followed by velvety tannins and a long, intense and mineral finish. <strong>(94 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>2014 Domaine Duroch\u00e9 Griotte-Chambertin</strong><br>\nSeventy bottles made. Fabulous transparent, purple, shinning color. Ample body and very elegant, with a lovely core of cool fruit, layered texture , and a long scintillating finish. Extraordinary ! <strong>(95 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Roasted \u2018Anjou\u2019 pigeon with chicory and Roquefort</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2016 Domaine Robert Groffier Chambolle-Musigny 1er Cru Les Amoureuses</strong><br>\nChassis of rich, ripe tannins, in a glossy core of fruit. Beautifully elegant and refined - this will develop beautifully ! <strong>(93 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>2007 Giuseppe Quintarelli Amarone della Valpolicella Classico</strong><br>\nQuite gourmand palate and intense concentration, more power and structure, with firm tannins and wild fruit. <strong>(92 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Vacherin Mont d\u2019Or with white chocolate and mango</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2015 Von Schubert Maximin Gr\u00fcnh\u00e4user Abtsberg Riesling Auslese Nr. 24</strong><br>\nAromas of orange zest, confit lemon with chewy extract and tense concentration. <strong>(90 pts.)</strong>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>2005 Fritz Haag Brauneberger Juffer-Sonnenuhr Riesling Beerenauslese</strong><br>\ncorked <em><strong>NR (flawed)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
